  <!-- virtual_base: aligns v6's wrist-mounted base_link to the GeoRT
       template convention (X = palm normal, Y = palm to thumb, Z = palm to
       middle finger), AND moves the origin to the middle-finger MCP — the
       same reference frame allegro_right uses, which is required for
       chamfer-loss matching against the human mocap data.

       Translation: virtual_base sits at v6's middle-finger MCP, at
         (0, -0.00125, 0.1125) in the original base_link frame.
       Rotation: +90 deg around Z so v6 +X (thumb side) → +Y (template),
         and v6 -Y (palm normal) → +X (template).
       After expressing the original base_link pose in virtual_base coords:
         xyz = R_z(+pi/2) * (0, +0.00125, -0.1125) = (-0.00125, 0, -0.1125)
         rpy = (0, 0, +pi/2) -->
